originalText.text:
I cannot recommend Teddy enough.

My wife and I are first-time home buyers, and Teddy did an amazing job leading us through the process, from our initial scattershot search across multiple neighborhoods to the final details of the close, even recommending movers and a cleaning service. His knowledge of New York real estate is deep. He is nonjudgemental, patient, and readily available to answer questions or offer sound counsel. Most important, he never once pressured us. It was clearly important to him that we found the right thing for *us*, no matter how long that was going to take.

We completely trusted him to navigate the coop board application. He went above and beyond, making sure every T was crossed and every I was dotted and that we looked as good as we possibly could.

Throughout the process, he maintained an unflappable air of zen-like calm, even when the two of us were FREAKING out. Now we are the proud owners of what we believe is the greatest apartment in New York City. Could not have done it without Teddy.
